{
  "stem": "150.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was too young to go to work in the ghetto, so I don't know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I know that he was a big macher in the construction.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When we got to the concentration camp, Berkman also almost immediately became leader of a brigade.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He spoke perfect German.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And apparently, he knew enough about how this whole thing worked to the point where eventually he rose to be the head, from the prisoners' side, of a whole shift construction project, and eventually, the head of the entire construction project from the prisoners' side, to the point where he even had a German car and driver that drove him around, around the project, and he coordinated the prisoners, who worked when and what, and what's priority and what isn't, and straighten up screw-ups and all that.",
      "word_count": 87
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Extremely dangerous-- you know, the first screw up, they'd shoot them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That would be that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And yet he managed to gain their confidence to the point where he managed to convince them that it is not efficient to have two 12 hour shifts, that it would be much more efficient to have three eight-hour shifts.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I don't know why.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, labor was not a problem, unless maybe it was becoming a problem.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they had plenty of labor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What do they care if people died?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Berkman managed to convince them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As far as I know, it has never happened anywhere in any other labor camp where they changed people to eight hour shifts.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the expected happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People stopped dying.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, he must have saved hundreds and hundreds of lives.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It happened about three, maybe four months before the end of the war where we shifted to three eight hour shifts.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was much more complicated for the Germans, I'm sure.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
